SOVIET CRISIS AND ARMAMENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
So officials of the Soviet Union have decided to tell the citizens of that 
country the truth about the breakdown of their system for the distribution of 
consumer goods! It was news to me, also. Recent articles in The Times have 
painted a picture of such gross mismanagement, confusion and bad faith that I 
think we should re-evaluate our alliances and priorities in foreign relations. 
</P>
<P>
Mr. President and Congress, the Soviet Union is down for the count! The Soviets 
are no longer a threat, as they can't even get their trains and trucks to run! 
It's time to stop spending money to defend our nation against an old "enemy" 
which is so gravely ailing. 
</P>
