<HEADLINE>
<P>
DOMINGUEZ DRAWS RUGGED SOCCER FOE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Second-ranked Cal State Dominguez Hills will play fourth-rated Keene State of 
New Hampshire on Nov. 11 in the opening game of the NCAA Division II Women's 
Soccer Championships at Barry College in Miami. 
</P>
<P>
Only four teams, one from each NCAA geographic area, advance to the 
championships. The winner between Dominguez Hills (18-2) and Keene (13-3-2) 
will play the winner between host Barry (15-0-2) and Adelphi University of New 
York (8-6-1) for the national title Nov. 12. Barry is ranked No. 1 and Adelphi 
is ranked 6th. 
</P>
<P>
Keene is very physical, a non-stop team and well-coached, said Dominguez Hills 
Coach Marine Cano. "We will have to force them to make key mistakes," he said. 
</P>
<P>
Both Dominguez Hills losses were to UC Santa Barbara, a Division I team. 
</P>
</TEXT>
