<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLOTHESLINES: SHRUG OFF THE FUR TRIM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARYLOU LUTHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Question: Are fur-trimmed coats fashionable now? I have an old sable shrug that 
could become the collar and cuffs on a cloth coat, but I hate to go to the 
expense if the look is dated. 
</P>
<P>
H.I. 
</P>
<P>
Answer: Fur collars and cuffs are not exactly the last work in coats, but fur 
sleeves are. How about taking a page from Paris designer Christian Lacroix's 
sketchbook and converting your shrug to sleeves, as illustrated here? 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Drawing, FERNANDO FLORES 
