<HEADLINE>
<P>
PLANE CRASH KILLS BRAZILIAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Brazilian air force turboprop plane Thursday crashed into a beer warehouse 
shortly after takeoff in the southern city of Curitiba, and the pilot died 
after ejecting from the aircraft, officials said. The cause of the crash was 
under investigation. The pilot tried to parachute to safety but was fatally 
injured in the fall, they said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
