<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: ARTHUR ANDERSEN NAMES HEAD OF WESTERN OPERATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PATRICK LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A. B. (Dick) Poladian has been named managing partner of Arthur Andersen &amp; 
Co.'s Southern California operations, replacing Sheldon I. Ausman, who retired 
last month. 
</P>
<P>
Poladian, 37, will manage Andersen's offices in Los Angeles, Orange County, San 
Diego, Las Vegas and Honolulu. 
</P>
<P>
Poladian joined the accounting firm in 1974 and has been a partner in 
Andersen's tax division for the last five years. 
</P>
<P>
Separately, Andersen Consulting, the accounting firm's sister company, named 
Barry Patmore managing partner of Southern California operations. PATRICK LEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
