<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
McKesson Corp. has promoted Alan Seelenfreund to chairman and chief executive, 
replacing Thomas Field, who abruptly resigned in September. The San 
Francisco-based drug wholesale and distribution company also promoted Rex 
Malson, formerly executive vice president-operations, to president and chief 
operating officer. The two longtime McKesson executives will share 
responsibilities under a newly created office of the chief executive. 
Seelenfreund, 52, formerly was executive vice president and chief financial 
officer. He joined the company in 1975. Malson, 57, joined the company in 1973 
and was named executive vice president in 1986 after serving as president of 
the company's Drug and Health-Care Group. 
</P>
</TEXT>
