<TEXT>
<P>
Eastman Kodak Co.: The Rochester, N.Y. photographic, chemicals and plastics 
firm, which also owns Sterling Drug Inc., reported that third-quarter net 
income dropped 25% from a year ago to $329 million. Sales totaled a record 
$5.11 billion, up 2%. The results were attributed to higher operating costs and 
the unfavorable impact of foreign currency rate changes. 
