<HEADLINE>
<P>
A SELECTED GUIDE TO MILLINERY SHOPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOANNA DENDEL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hats by Ahadi: 733 N. La Brea Ave; 10:30 a.m. to 6:30 p.m. Monday through 
Saturday or by appointment, (213) 965-0639. 
</P>
<P>
Ahadi's hats follow fashion trends. This season he trims them with tassels and 
crusader crosses. Prices: $45-$300. 
</P>
<P>
The Hat Gallery: 5632 Melrose Ave.; 11 a.m. to 7 p.m. Tuesday through Saturday, 
(213) 463-3163. 
</P>
<P>
Elizabeth Marcel's hats have turn-of-the-century crowns and distinctive antique 
trims. Prices: $175-$250. 
</P>
<P>
Imolden Grey: 2409 Main St., Santa Monica; 11:30 a.m. to 6 p.m. Tuesday through 
Saturday, noon to 5 p.m. Sunday, (213) 396-0285. 
</P>
<P>
Imolden Grey's hats recall English garden parties. They're trimmed with antique 
flowers, ribbons and lace. The store also carries a small collection of hats by 
other designers. Prices: $85-$250. 
</P>
<P>
Patina Millinery: 119 N. La Brea; noon to 6 p.m., Wednesday through Saturday or 
by appointment, (213) 931-6931. 
</P>
<P>
Romance rules and there are feathers everywhere. These hats are a movie 
costumer's dream. Prices: $185-$325. 
</P>
<P>
Studio Rabbitworks Flora: 8808 Melrose Ave., West Hollywood; by appointment 
only, (213) 276-4407. 
</P>
<P>
Rosemary Warren uses old hats from defunct milliners and embellishes them with 
antique ribbons, buckles and bows. She also makes collapsible fabric hats that 
look like they're from grandmother's attic. Prices: $175-$250. JOANNA DENDEL 
</P>
</TEXT>
