</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: RADIO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Snyder on KWNK: Tom Snyder is back on the Los Angeles air waves, heard nightly 
from 7 to 10 on KWNK-AM (670), a San Fernando Valley-based talk station. 
Snyder's nationally syndicated radio show was dropped by KABC-AM last spring 
because of excessive pre-emptions during the baseball season. KWNK is also 
starting a new magazine-format news and entertainment morning show that will 
feature Dick McInnes from 6 to 9 a.m., replacing Randy Kerdoon who went to 
KFWB. McInnes, who got his start working for Rona Barrett and co-authored the 
autobiography of Dorothy Lamour, also interviews soap opera stars Saturdays 
from 12 to 1 p.m. on a KWNK show called "S.O.A.P." ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA110389-0108 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 129572 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
November 3, 1989, Friday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Calendar; Part F; Page 2; Column 1; Entertainment Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
