<P>
Coming Attractions: Producer David Wolper, the force behind TV epics such as 
"Roots" and "The Thorn Birds," is developing a movie about the Northern 
California earthquake for ABC. Wolper is in the early stages of research and 
will focus on acts of heroism connected with the devastating temblor. CBS and 
NBC said they have no plans to produce movies based on the Oct. 17 tragedy. . . 
. The Universal Pictures comedy "Uncle Buck," which has grossed $61 million so 
far, is headed for life as a CBS sitcom. Writer-producer Tim O'Connell is 
developing the project. ALEENE MacMINN 
