8 JORDANIAN SOLDIERS KILLED IN COPTER CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
AMMAN, Jordan 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The commander of the armed forces in southern Jordan and seven other military 
men were killed Thursday in a helicopter crash about 60 miles southwest of 
Amman, the government-run radio announced. 
</P>
<P>
Brig. Saoud Maghsoub Harahsheh was among the eight soldiers and officers who 
died in the accident, state-run Jordan Radio reported. 
</P>
<P>
It did not give the cause of the accident, but a senior army official, speaking 
on condition of anonymity, said it was apparently caused by a technical defect. 
More details were not immediately available. 
