<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Safeguard Health Enterprises Inc., the Anaheim-based provider of fixed-fee 
dental care plans, reported that net income declined 18% for the third quarter, 
to $717,000 from $871,000 for the 1988 third quarter. Revenue dropped 11%, to 
$15.3 million from $17.1 million. Net income for the first nine months totaled 
$2.4 million, 4% lower than the $2.4 million posted a year earlier. Revenue 
declined 9%, to $46.5 million from $51 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
