<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP LP CHART; 
</P>
<P>
JANET JACKSON SPENDS ANOTHER WEEK AT NO. 1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS HUNT, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Janet Jackson seems fairly secure in the No. 1 position on the Billboard pop 
album chart with "Rhythm Nation 1814," which is in its third week on top. The 
big news on the pop singles chart is that those torrid teen idols New Kids on 
the Block now have two singles in the Top 10 at the same time -- "Cover Girl" 
(No. 3) and "Didn't I (Blow Your Mind)" (No. 9). This is one of rarest -- and 
most impressive -- feats in all of pop chartdom. 
</P>
<P>
* Linda Ronstadt's "Cry Like a Rainstorm, Howl Like the Wind" is headed for the 
pop Top 10. This album, featuring Aaron Neville, shot up to No. 20 in four 
weeks, a rapid rise for a collection of ballads. The album's first single, 
"Don't Know Much," is No. 18 and also Top-10 bound. 
</P>
