<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Tall Tales Some of the children showed up in their pajamas, but it 
didn't turn out to be the kind of story hour that would put anyone to sleep. 
Carolyn Steidinger brought her tales to life with a variety of puppets that 
delighted the youngsters in her audience at Fullerton Public Library. 
Steidinger doesn't stand behind a puppet stage. Instead, she brings her 
colorful characters close to the audience to encourage the children to 
interact. Above, Steidinger and Pete the Pelican, who only eats things that 
begin with the letter P, entertain the children. At left, Marc Whipple, 5, 
enjoys the show. GARY AMBROSE / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
