WORLD; 
</P>
<P>
CANADA UNVEILS ABORTION BILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
OTTAWA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Canadian government unveiled an abortion law today that allows a woman to 
end her pregnancy at any time if a doctor believes her life or health is 
threatened. 
</P>
<P>
The long-awaited legislation will fill the void created when Canada's Supreme 
Court struck down a more restrictive law last year but will end what has become 
a practice of abortion on demand that resulted from the lack of an abortion 
law. 
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Brian Mulroney's government had promised new legislation since 
the previous law was declared unconstitutional in January, 1988. 
</P>
<P>
"The bill introduced today establishes that the question of abortion is a 
medical decision to be made between a woman and her doctor, based on health 
grounds," Justice Minister Doug Lewis told reporters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
