<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRAD PEARCE, TOP-SEED GUNNARSSON ADVANCE IN BERGEN OPEN TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BERGEN, Norway 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
American qualifier Brad Pearce of Provo, Utah, and top-seeded Jan Gunnarsson of 
Sweden scored semifinal victories today in the Bergen Open tennis 
championships. 
</P>
<P>
Pearce defeated Niklas Kulti of Sweden, the world's top-ranked junior player, 
4-6, 6-4, 7-6 (7-4). The 23-year-old American trailed 4-1 in the third set. 
</P>
<P>
Gunnarsson, who is seeking his first Bergen Open title in five straight 
attempts, eliminated Kelly Jones of San Diego 6-4, 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
The title match will be played Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
